    • Method Detail

      • compose

        Response compose(YADAQueryResult[] yadaQueryResults)
                 throws YADAResponseException,
                        YADAConverterException
        Use to access the raw results stored in yadaQueryResults, establish the Response structure and initiate population of the object via create(), and fill the object via one of the append methods

        The difference between compose(YADAQueryResult[]) and create() is somewhat academic. compose enables the caller, typically Service to pass the YADAQueryResults associated to a YADAQuery to the Response, whereas create() does not. Theoretically, compose(YADAQueryResult[]) could do everything create() does, but the added granularity makes it a bit easier to code.

        Parameters:
        yadaQueryResults - array containing result objects
        Returns:
        this Response object
        Throws:
        YADAResponseException - when response composition fails
        YADAConverterException - when result reformatting fails
        See Also:
        JSONResponse
